The paper discusses molecular communication in regulated biological systems, which involves the encoding and transmission of information about the state of the system. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.MA), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper focuses on blood pressure measurement, which is a topic in both theoretical and quantitative biology (q-bio.TO) and quantitative methods in biomolecules (q-bio.QM).
